## Backend Setup

cd backend
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
### Create Database

CREATE DATABASE support_ticket_db;
### Configure .env

DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/support_ticket_db
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key
ALGORITHM=HS256
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=60
### Run the Server

uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 9000
- API Base URL: http://127.0.0.1:9000
- Swagger Docs: http://127.0.0.1:9000/docs

---

## Frontend Setup

cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
- Frontend URL: http://127.0.0.1:5173

---

## Authentication

JWT-based authentication is used throughout the system. All protected endpoints require the token to be sent in the request header:

Authorization: Bearer <token>
---

## Ticket Workflow

Open  -->  In Progress  -->  Resolved  -->  Closed
Rules:
- Customers can only view their own tickets
- Only Admins and Support Agents can update ticket status
- Invalid status transitions are restricted
- Resolution time is tracked automatically

---

## API Endpoints

### Auth
| Method | Endpoint       | Description           |
|--------|----------------|-----------------------|
| POST   | /auth/register | Register a new user   |
| POST   | /auth/login    | Login and get token   |
| GET    | /auth/me       | Get current user info |

### Tickets

| Method | Endpoint                  | Description         |
|--------|---------------------------|---------------------|
| POST   | /tickets                  | Create a ticket     |
| GET    | /tickets                  | List all tickets    |
| GET    | /tickets/{id}             | Get ticket details  |
| PATCH  | /tickets/{id}/assign      | Assign an agent     |
| PATCH  | /tickets/{id}/status      | Update status       |

### Comments

| Method | Endpoint                     | Description       |
|--------|------------------------------|-------------------|
| POST   | /tickets/{id}/comments       | Add a comment     |
| GET    | /tickets/{id}/comments       | Get all comments  |

### Notifications

| Method | Endpoint        | Description           |
|--------|-----------------|-----------------------|
| GET    | /notifications  | Get user notifications|

### Admin

| Method | Endpoint          | Description           |
|--------|-------------------|-----------------------|
| GET    | /admin/analytics  | Get dashboard metrics |

---

## Database Schema

### Users

| Field    | Type    |
|----------|---------|
| id       | Integer |
| name     | String  |
| email    | String  |
| password | String  |
| role     | String  |

### Tickets

| Field             | Type     |
|-------------------|----------|
| id                | Integer  |
| title             | String   |
| description       | Text     |
| priority          | String   |
| status            | String   |
| customer_id       | Integer  |
| assigned_agent_id | Integer  |
| created_at        | DateTime |
| resolved_at       | DateTime |

### Comments

| Field      | Type     |
|------------|----------|
| id         | Integer  |
| message    | Text     |
| ticket_id  | Integer  |
| user_id    | Integer  |
| created_at | DateTime |

### Notifications

| Field      | Type     |
|------------|----------|
| id         | Integer  |
| message    | String   |
| user_id    | Integer  |
| created_at | DateTime |

---

## Notifications

Notifications are triggered on the following events:
- Ticket assignment
- Ticket status updates
- New comment added

Each user receives only notifications relevant to them.

---

## Admin Dashboard

The admin analytics endpoint provides the following metrics:
- Total ticket count
- Status distribution across all tickets
- Priority distribution across all tickets
- Average resolution time

---

## Frontend Highlights

- Clean dashboard layout with role-based navigation
- Ticket cards displaying status and priority at a glance
- Chat-style comment interface for support conversations
- Auto-refreshing notification panel
- Fully responsive UI with mobile support

---

## Conclusion

This project demonstrates a complete support ticket workflow system with a robust backend, role-based access control, structured status transitions, and a clean frontend interface — suitable for real-world applications and portfolio demonstration.